    Validator

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DuplicateAttributeException
    A duplicate attribute exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown if an object -already contains a certain attribute -cannot contain the attribute twice
    EmptyObjectException
    An empty object exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when an object is undesirably empty.
    EmptyStringException
    An empty string exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a string is undesirably an empty string.
    InvalidStateException
    An invalid state exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when an object is in a undesired, unknown, undesired, invalid state because of an other unsuccessful operation.
    InvalidValueException
    An invalid value exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value is not valid.
    NegativeValueException
    A negative value exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value is undesirable negative.
    NonPositiveValueException
    A non positive value exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value is undesirable not positive.
    NonRepresentationException
    A non representation exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when an object does undesirable not represent an other object.
    StoppedObjectException
    A stopped object exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when it is not known that a object is stopped.
    UnequalValueException
    An unequal value exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value does not equal a desired value.
    UnexistingAttributeException
    A unexisting attribute exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when an object does not have a requested attribute.
    ValueNotInRangeException
    A value out of range exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value is not in a desired range.
    ValueUnderMinException
    A value under min exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value is smaller than a possible minimum.
    ZeroValueException
    A zero value exception is an exception that is intended to be thrown when a value is undesirably zero.
